gujarati.context:
Here are the two Gujarati couplets translated into English:

Ukō harjī Rāmjī dōy, kṛṣīkār karmaśī soy;
Jōdhō jēthō mēghō Hari-nātha, Bhagō arjaṇ bijalō sātha.

becomes:

One who knows Ram's joy, does good deeds with diligence; 
The one who knows God's path, has His blessing always with them.

This is the translation:

This great beginning is of many, forever praised by the Lord; 
Purana of Dinaanath's ancient tale, whose extent is equal to the Vani.

Here are the translations:

My mind's karma makes it a servant, such is its determination within; 
Whoever knows this, becomes His Majesty's true devotee, and does what He wills.

Live like a wolf's prey, know the divine norms; 
even then worship the Lord by His own power; 
the best thing is that which takes away, touch the Lord who has taken away.

The two couplets are:

In the city, a brahmin is many, worships Hari when not busy; 
False accounts are written by a cunning merchant, takes away even an Amarshi's (immortal being) one.
